name: Mariah Carey
summary: In a tragic turn of events, singer Mariah Carey announced the passing of both her mother, Patricia Carey, and her sister, Alison Carey, on the same day. The news has left Carey heartbroken, as she expressed her grief in a statement to People magazine. Alison Carey, 63, passed away in Coxsackie, New York, while the date of her mother's passing was not disclosed. Carey's mother, Patricia, had been battling Alzheimer's disease. The double loss has devastated Carey, prompting her to share her sorrow with the public.

name: Tulsi Gabbard
summary: Former Democratic Congresswoman Tulsi Gabbard, who ran for the party's nomination in 2020, has endorsed former President Donald Trump for the 2024 presidential election. Gabbard, who left the Democratic Party and now identifies as an independent, cited her belief that Trump is the best candidate to address issues such as foreign policy, energy, and election integrity. Her endorsement has been met with criticism from some Democrats, who view it as a betrayal of her former party. However, Gabbard has defended her decision, stating that she believes Trump is the best choice to lead the country.

name: CeeDee Lamb
summary: CeeDee Lamb, the star wide receiver for the Dallas Cowboys, has ended his contract holdout and agreed to a lucrative multi-year deal with the team. According to various sources, the contract is reportedly worth $136 million over four years, including a record-setting bonus. Cowboys owner Jerry Jones had previously expressed confidence that Lamb would sign an agreement, despite the holdout, and the expectations have now been fulfilled. This extension signals a significant investment in Lamb, who has emerged as a key playmaker for the Cowboys' offense. The deal ensures his continued presence on the team and provides him with substantial financial compensation for his contributions.

name: Aaron Judge
summary: Aaron Judge, the New York Yankees' outfielder, continues to make history with his extraordinary home run hitting. After recently hitting his 50th and 51st homers, Judge is on pace to surpass 63 homers this season. He has become the fifth player in MLB history to have three seasons with 50 or more home runs and is on track for one of the greatest individual seasons in Major League Baseball history. Judge's accomplishments have garnered praise and inspiration, with many experts and fans marveling at his achievements. He has also faced some criticism from a Little League coach for allegedly ignoring children, but the Yankees have come to his defense. Despite this minor setback, Judge remains focused on his pursuit of home run history, leaving many to wonder if he can surpass the legendary Babe Ruth's single-season record of 60 home runs.

summary: Various news articles highlight topics related to prominent figures and entertainment. One article centers around Kamala Harris, Madonna, and Cher, exploring the societal implications of addressing women. Another covers the upcoming "Cher & Cher Alike" show in 2024. The "Beat Goes On" tour features Lisa McClowry impersonating Cher. A Yahoo Life article discusses Cher's endorsement of flared pants, while a Daily Mail story reports on her son's substance use. A legal dispute between Cher and Sonny Bono's widow over royalties is reported on by MSN. Military history is touched upon with an article on Signal Corps pigeon recognition during wars. Architectural Digest showcases the most memorable movie closets, including Cher's. Yahoo Movies UK reveals Cher's decision to restart work on her biopic. Additionally, MSN highlights Julianne Hough's emotional experience working with Cher on the film "Burlesque."

name: Novak Djokovic
summary: Novak Djokovic is aiming to make history at the 2024 US Open by claiming a record 25th Grand Slam title. The Serbian tennis star will open the tournament's night session on Monday and will face Radu Albot in the first round. Djokovic is coming off an Olympic gold medal win and is determined to add to his impressive tally of major championships. The US Open will be the final Grand Slam event of 2024, and Djokovic will be the reigning champion after his victory in 2023. Fans can catch all the action live on various platforms, including CBS News, Sports Illustrated, Yahoo Sports, and The New York Times.

name: Coco Gauff
summary: Coco Gauff, the 2023 US Open champion, is facing challenges this year as she struggles to retain her title. Despite being featured on Wheaties boxes and having her second signature shoe released with New Balance, Gauff has had a rough start to the 2024 season. Experts believe she needs a mental break to improve her performance. However, she was recently honored by Billie Jean King at a US Open event, which she will now be defending. Tennis legends like Chris Evert and John McEnroe have expressed their thoughts on her chances of defending her title.

name: Christopher Reeve
summary: A new documentary, "Super/Man: The Christopher Reeve Story," is set to premiere, offering a glimpse into the life of the late actor known for his iconic role as Superman. The trailer gives a preview of Reeve's acting career, his accident that left him paralyzed, and his subsequent journey as an advocate for people with disabilities. The documentary features interviews with Reeve's family and friends, who share their memories and insights into his life both before and after the accident. The title "Super/Man" highlights the duality of Reeve's existence, showcasing his strength and resilience in the face of adversity.

name: Danny Jansen
summary: In a historic MLB first, Danny Jansen became the first player to officially play for two teams in the same game. He started as a catcher for the Toronto Blue Jays and was later traded to the Boston Red Sox. Jansen then played for the Blue Jays again as a designated hitter in the same game. This unprecedented switcheroo made MLB history and garnered widespread attention and coverage in news outlets such as The Associated Press, MLB.com, ESPN, and Fox Sports.
